-- Filter results to only show results with:
--   minSoldUnits: only count products with that many sales
--   maxListedProducts: only count merchants with at most this many listed products. Set a negative number to disable this filter.
--   minListedProducts: same as max
column2: but filters those that have at least this amount of listed products.\n--\n--   /!\\ NOTE: minSoldUnits will be applied first

then the other 2 filters.
--       This means that minSoldUnits==1000 and minListedProducts==2 will show sellers who
--       sold at least 1000 units of each of at least 2 articles.


DECLARE ?minSoldUnits AS INTEGER = -1
DECLARE ?minListedProducts AS INTEGER = 1
DECLARE ?maxListedProducts AS INTEGER = -1

    SELECT merchant_id

count(1) as nbProds
    FROM summer_products_with_rating_and_performance_2020_08

    )

  merchantId

(
SELECT 
  prods.merchant_id as merchantId

SUM( CASE WHEN has_urgency_banner = 1 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END ) AS urgencyProductsCount


FROM summer_products_with_rating_and_performance_2020_08 as prods
LEFT OUTER JOIN 
sellerProdsCountTable as pcs
ON prods.merchant_id = pcs.merchant_id

WHERE
  pcs.nbProds >= ?minListedProducts
  AND
  (?maxListedProducts < 1 OR (pcs.nbProds <= ?maxListedProducts) )
  AND
  prods.units_sold >= ?minSoldUnits

GROUP by prods.merchant_id
) as base
